## What the Screen Should Be

**"StyleSphere — Green Transition Dashboard"**

Think of it as a board-level view. Everything the client has set in motion, now visible as live progress. Three sections:

---

### Section 1 — Transition Progress at a Glance
Top row of 4 live metric cards:

- **ESG Score** — 42 baseline → 58 current → 74 projected. Progress bar with trajectory line.
- **Scope 3 Reduced** — 0 tCO₂e → 3,840 tCO₂e reduced so far. Percentage of 18% target achieved.
- **Suppliers Transitioning** — 6 of 14 high-risk suppliers actively on roadmap.
- **Value Unlocked** — $180K cost savings activated. $240K revenue pipeline open.

---

### Section 2 — HSBC Relationship Value
This is what makes the screen uniquely HSBC. Show three cards:

- **Green Loan Active** — $2M facility drawn for Coats Holdings transition. Rate: 3.9%.
- **Green Bond Eligibility** — ESG score reaches 74 in Month 12. Bond issuance unlocked.
- **RM Last Contact** — Pre-filled brief sent 3 days ago. Next review scheduled.

---

### Section 3 — Live Regulatory & Market Intelligence
A compact feed showing:

- New regulatory update relevant to StyleSphere surfaced today
- One new government subsidy program detected in their region
- One new premium buyer program now accessible based on current ESG progress

---

## Why This Is the Right Last Screen

It answers the three things judges are looking for at the end of a client journey:

**Resilience** — supplier transition progress and regulatory alerts show ongoing risk is being managed.

**Cost savings** — green loan rate and ESG-linked savings are visible and quantified.

**Revenue** — buyer programs and green bond eligibility show commercial upside being unlocked.

It also shows HSBC's ongoing role — not just a one-time setup but a continuous relationship platform. The client has a reason to come back every week.

